Initial support to allow WebQuery to request SQL logging, this will place prepared statements (N.B. with ? in place of parameters) in the ConstrainedResultSet which may be logged or returned to the user depending on the application. This is implemented using a Hibernate Interceptor that observes everything going on and which has a specific hook for logging prepared statements against one or more ThreadLocal Consumer<String>s

Rewrite QCriteriaBuilder such that there's no conditional appending, instead there's the ability to clear various parts of the query. This commit also refactors the conversion of WebQuery to QCriteriaBuilder into the constructor of QCriteriaBuilder.

N.B. Certain queries could save the conversion penalty by adding a clone() method to QCriteriaBuilder and then clearing certain aspects of the cloned result (but this is a tiny minority of the queries executed by the system so unlikely to make much difference in the real world)
